column17: This peptide is one of the 16-mer peptides (overlapping by 8 residues) covering the complete M. tuberculosis  65-kDa Hsp protein studied to find binding motifs to MHC class II I-E<sup>g7</sup> molecules.
Epitope occurs within protective antigen (PA63) mature chain. PA83 contains PA20 and PA63.  Swiss-Prot positions reflect precursor sequence numbering.

The epitope possesses a non-standard PΩ anchor residue AlaP10 forming a set of conserved hydrogen bonds with MHC side chains. The peptide rises above the floor of the binding site and kinks between AlaP6 and SerP8. Consequently, AlaP7 is completely solvent-exposed. Only hydrogen bonds crucial for the conformation of C-terminal part of the peptide are discussed in the paper and curated. They result in an overall shift of the peptide backbone towards the alpha2-helix of MHC, when compared to other H-2D(b)-bound peptides.
